The server www.bankovnipoplatky.com, which conducts a public survey every year on the most absurd bank charges, has now decided to launch the contest of the settlement or ideas from the most absurd "EU workshop".
"The fact that the EU has recently considered adopting a quota of 40 per cent of women for the management of large European companies was at the root of our decision," said Patrik Nacher, the organizer of the survey.
Among the absurdities mentioned is already, for example, the recent decision of the European Court to unify insurance premiums for men and women.
So far, however, women have been at an advantage in terms of life insurance rates because they objectively pose less risk to insurance companies.
People can report until the end of the year any other such incredible idea of the "EU workshop".
“The vote will take place before the end of February 2013,” Nacher said.
Controversial EU regulations include, for example, the requirement to add biocomponents to fuels, which has harmful consequences for the environment, or the prohibition on the use of reliable mercury thermometers, only because they contain a relatively small amount of a dangerous substance, or the directive on the size of hen cages, which has led to the price increase.
Criticism has also been expressed in the past against the de facto ban on the use of the term "spreading butter" or the withdrawal of the sale of conventional bulbs.
Quality bananas should be 14 centimeters in size.
