People want me to save the Republic, but I'm just an amateur, says Senator Okamura
Mr. Speaker, how did you come up with the idea of running for president?
It is not being a senator or a president that matters to me.
If everything worked smoothly in our country, I would not be a candidate anywhere.
But I can’t stand to see how the country has been looted for the last twenty years, that thieves are not under lock and key, and taxes and retirement ages are rising.
